    "argue that black-box detection might be unachievable when LLMs can produce text completely indistinguishable from human-generated content (Sadasivan et al., 2023).",
    "Chakraborty et al.",
    "show that detection is theoretically possible if machine-and human-generated content distributions differ, but as LLMs advance, the sample size required for detection increases (Chakraborty et al., 2023).",
    "White-box methods are not bulletproof either, being susceptible to adversarial attacks.",
    "Recent studies suggest that text paraphrasing significantly reduces detection accuracy (Sadasivan et al., 2023; Krishna et al., 2024)."
